# Analysis of Discord Chat in "üí¨-discussion" Channel

## 1. Summary
The discussion primarily revolves around concerns about ElizaOS token price decline (reportedly 86% since migration) and questions about project direction. Community members express frustration about lack of communication regarding token utility and roadmap clarity. Team representatives (particularly Kenk and jasyn_bjorn) provide limited updates about upcoming products, specifically mentioning "Eliza Cloud" - an AI-assisted development tool for building, deploying, and managing agents. They explain it will be a low-code agent builder for elizaOS with components that will open up for other agent frameworks. 

The team confirms they have vesting schedules on token allocations and only one small tranche has unlocked. They mention future revenue from Eliza Cloud will be used for buybacks, and hint at an OTC decentralized desk in development that will work with ELIZAOS tokens. There's also mention of projects like Babylon and Otako that are being developed by the team with potential airdrops for ELIZAOS holders.

Community sentiment is divided between frustrated investors questioning the token's utility and supporters defending the team's focus on development over communication. Moderators occasionally remove or warn users they perceive as spreading "FUD" without constructive feedback.

## 2. FAQ
Q: Has the team sold any tokens since migration? (asked by hildi) A: We have vesting on every bucket and believe only 1 tranche has unlocked a small amount, so that would be a no on the selling. (answered by jasyn_bjorn)
Q: Do people need to pay in ElizaOS to use ElizaOS Cloud? (asked by crypto) A: Unanswered
Q: When is the Babylon airdrop due? (asked by Lexpo4777) A: Soon. On or about. (answered by The Light)
Q: Is there any latest update on Degenai? What is babylon. Is that a new token launched by shaw? (asked by @Jack) A: Unanswered
Q: What is the best route to buy [ElizaOS]? (asked by Figure) A: I use USDT on BSC in pancake swap. You can buy your gas fee for starting from a cex. (answered by Omid Sa)
Q: Were ElizaOS and AI16z two different projects before merger, OR AI16z renamed into ElizaOS? (asked by Rainman) A: Unanswered
Q: How do I get my agent to work properly without spending hundreds of $$$ for pro API access? (asked by SOLitude) A: Unanswered
Q: What will be impact on the price action [of Eliza Cloud launch]? (asked by Shaa07dy) A: Revenue, buybacks and burns, fame and visibility. (answered by Omid Sa)

# Discord Chat Analysis for üí¨-coders Channel

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily revolves around two technical issues. First, FenrirFawks is experiencing an error when deploying a Starknet unruggable meme token through a plugin, specifically a "Failed to parse String to BigInt" error. Odilitime suggests it could be related to JSON.stringify operations or BigInt parsing direction. FenrirFawks eventually shares modified code with Odilitime for debugging.

The second issue concerns Twitter API rate limits affecting the Twitter plugin functionality. SOLitude questions whether X (Twitter) changed something that requires expensive Pro API access. Roman V confirms that X implemented strict rate limits earlier in the year, making the API prohibitively expensive. Odilitime later mentions that plugin-Twitter works fine with a $200/month account using the 1.x branch.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: How can I get my agent to work with Twitter without spending hundreds for pro API access? (asked by SOLitude) A: They just came out with pay for only what you use recently (answered by jin)
Q: Is the Twitter functionality dead for Eliza right now? (asked by SOLitude) A: plugin-Twitter is working fine for me and the $200/mo account. I just cloned the plugin-twitter 1.x branch (answered by Odilitime)
Q: What is this tickets BS? (asked by SOLitude) A: Tickets BS is scammers trying to get you, ignore them (answered by Roman V)
Q: Where can I find ElizaOS Twitter account? (asked by Yoda) A: https://x.com/elizaecofund or https://x.com/elizaosc, our main one is currently suspended: https://x.com/elizaos (answered by Odilitime)

## 3. Help Interactions:
Helper: Odilitime | Helpee: FenrirFawks | Context: Error "Failed to parse String to BigInt" when deploying Starknet unruggable meme token | Resolution: Odilitime offered to review the code, suggested checking JSON.stringify operations and BigInt parsing direction
Helper: Roman V | Helpee: SOLitude | Context: Questions about Twitter "tickets BS" and API rate limits | Resolution: Explained these were scammers and provided context on X's rate limit changes
Helper: jin | Helpee: SOLitude | Context: Twitter API pricing concerns | Resolution: Informed about new pay-as-you-go pricing model
Helper: Odilitime | Helpee: SOLitude | Context: Twitter plugin functionality | Resolution: Confirmed plugin-Twitter works with $200/month account using 1.x branch

# Discord Chat Analysis for "core-devs" Channel

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily focused on technical observations and sharing of resources. Odilitime identified a large disk space usage issue in the CLI package (17GB), discovering that database files were being copied multiple times in project-starter templates. Jin shared ideas about interoperability between ElizaOS plugins and agent skills, suggesting a composability approach rather than building a new TUI from scratch. Several external resources were shared, including papers on tool composition, the AutoMaker project, and a CVE RCE exploit in n8n. Stan mentioned plans to check and clean the disk space issue and later referenced auto migration from version 5. The conversation was primarily informational with limited interactive problem-solving.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Should openapi.json schema be published somewhere? (asked by jin) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions:
